### Setup Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@authToken = <your_token_here>

### 1. Register User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Open Items (All)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items

### 4. Get Open Items (Lost Only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items?category=lost

### 5. Get Open Items (Found Only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items?category=found

### 6. Create Lost Item (Needs Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "title": "Black Umbrella",
    "description": "Left a black umbrella in the library",
    "details": ["Brand: Totes", "Color: Black", "Condition: Slightly used"],
    "category": "lost",
    "location": "Library 2nd Floor"
}

### 7. Create Found Item (Needs Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "title": "Student ID Card",
    "description": "Found an ID card near the cafeteria",
    "details": ["Name on ID: John Doe", "ID number: 123456"],
    "category": "found",
    "location": "Cafeteria"
}

### 8. Resolve an Item (Needs Auth)
# Replace <item_id> with an actual Item's ID from step 3
PUT {{baseUrl}}/items/<item_id>/resolve
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "resolverName": "John Smith"
}

### 9. Get Leaderboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/leaderboard
